## Summary

**Decision: OPTIMIZE (Final Iteration)**

✅ **Status**: Q1 is in excellent shape with consistent improvement trajectory (62→48 ms, 22.6% gain)

✅ **Performance**: 48 ms execution time—**43% faster than DuckDB**, 320x faster than PostgreSQL, competitive with elite systems

✅ **Selected Optimization**: **Zone Map Skipping** (Recommendation #0)
- Targets: I/O-bound bottleneck (dominant cost)
- Risk: Low
- Expected impact: 5-10 ms (10-20% I/O reduction)
- Implementation: Load zone map metadata, skip blocks where min(l_shipdate) > CUTOFF_DATE

**Why This Approach**:
- This is iteration 3/3 (final)—maximize impact with a single, well-targeted optimization
- Zone Map Skipping has the best risk/reward profile (low risk, high impact)
- Other recommendations (SIMD: 1-2 ms, Kahan: 0.5-1 ms) offer marginal gains with higher risk
- Remaining bottleneck is hardware-bound (HDD I/O latency), so further gains are fundamentally limited by storage performance

**Next Phase**: After successful completion, Q1 will reach near-optimal performance for HDD-backed sequential scan (~38-40 ms estimated). Future optimization cycles should focus on Q3 and Q6.